# CacheLayer (optional)

Silent Cursor hooks call CacheLayer before/after allowlisted tools. **Do not** call `lookup_step` / `save_step` before every native tool — that adds overhead.

## When to use MCP tools

- Resuming a run: `run_status(run_id)`
- Explicit reuse of an expensive step the hooks may have missed
- Before a risky write: `check_conflict(intended_action, run_id)` if you want an extra guard

## Do not

- Call `lookup_step` before every `Read` / `Shell` / `Grep`
- Call CacheLayer tools before other CacheLayer tools
- Save secrets from env files
